1) create 2 instances(linux 2 instance) with key pairs
    a) create SG and edit indbound port open port 80 to 0.0.0.0/0
        and ssh --> 22 to my ip
        
    b) create instance no_ choose amazon linux2, choose SG created above, enable (auto-assign-public-ip),
provide the below under user date-->     launch instance
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
echo '<html><body><h1 style="color:Blue;">Welcome to CloudSpace website </h1></body></html>' > /var/www/html/index.html
    
2) create autoscaling
on the ec2 page on your left choose launch templates(upgrades version)/configuration
        a) copy the amiid of the amazon linux2 instance created on steps 1 
        b) give a name to you LC (launch templateS configuration)
        C) SPECIFIC INSTANCE TYPE, the above user data, the above SG, AND KEY pair , click create Launch Configuration
            
3) Create AUTOSCALING GROUP 
    a) give an name
    b) select your LG, VPC and Subnet in which the instance should be launched
    c) desired and min/max capacity, target policy --none--next--> create ASG
4) CREATE A CLOUDWATCH ALARM based on cpu
go to cloudwatch dashboard ---> create alarm--> choose metric--> ec2, by ASG, --> CHOOSE CPU METRIC FOR SCALE IN ( bigger <= CPU 80%  ) --> STATIC(THRESHOLD)--> NOTIFICATION (IN ALARM)--CREATE ALARM
---> DO THE FOR SCALE OUT(>15% FOR CPU ) you can create an sns topic, if you need to receive notification and subcribe to it 
5) create a target and choose the instance as target, --On the ec2 dasboard click create target group and choose the instance 
6) create a load balancer from the ec2 dashboard choose load balancer, create application load balancer --> name--internet facing--> select vpc, and at least 2 SUBNETS, 
CREATE AN ALB SG --> ON WHICH YOU OPEN PORT 80 TO 0.0.0.0/0 
CHOOSE THE SG while creating the ALB --> LISTENER WILL BE KEPT TO 80--> CLICK CREATE ALB